author: Richard Hartley-Parkinson For Metro.Co.Uk
title: Massive blob appears on Philippines that turns out to be a whale carcass | Metro News
text:
Richard Hartley-Parkinson for Metro.co.uk Friday 24 Feb 2017 6:08 am (Picture: Marjorie Cabatingan Aboy) 
Okay, internet detectives, here’s one for you: What the hell is this? 
A massive white blob has emerged days after an earthquake off the coast of the Philippines. 
The huge hairy beast appeared in Cagdainao, Dinagat Islands and has attracted quite a lot of attention from the locals. 
There are theories as to what it is, but nothing soldid as yet. (Picture: Marjorie Cabatingan Aboy) (Picture: Marjorie Cabatingan Aboy) 
The earthquake struck on Sunday and since then many carcasses have been washed up. 
Some believe that it may be a whale, others have suggested a polar bear. Or a whale/polar bear hybrid. Or a big Shih tzu. Witches are putting a spell on Donald Trump at midnight 
We think it looks a bit like an English sheepdog. 
When a mass of organic matter washes up on the shore like this it is referred to as a ‘globster’. 
By the way, the mystery has actually been solved. It’s the body of a whale and it’s in advanced decomposition. It’s believed to have died two weeks ago after being hit by a ship. (Picture: Marjorie Cabatingan Aboy)
